              "question_id": 1,
              "question": "Que 1) The role of emotional intelligence in value formation is often overlooked. In this context analyze the relationship between emotional intelligence and ethical decision-making. (8 Marks)",
              "student_answer": "Ans: Value formation is a moral process, not an emotional process, and is linked with family upbringing environment education, and society but we cannot overlook the role of emotional intelligence in developing it.\n\nRole of emotional intelligence in value formation can be seen as:\n\n1. It helps in conflict resolution. Emotionally intelligent people manage their anger frustration in peer pressure.\n\n2. Helps in ethical decision making: Emotionally intelligent officer rather takes more stable\n\ndecision than a normal person\n3. Improves communication\nunderstanding problems.\n\nIt is overlooked because of\nthe following reasons\n\n1. Society is more focus on money,\nfame and success\n\n2. Moral values are only taught\nin text books, not practiced.\n\n3. Traditional practices are just\nfor show off like for making\nreels, fb, instagram rather than\nlearning why these traditions are\ndesigned to practice.\n\nHence emotional\nintelligence is a thin line in\nmaking a smart plus sensitive,\nhigh valued officer, human being.\nwithout emotional intelligence\none cannot survive and tackle\nthe challenges.",
              "student_answer_summary": "The student attempts to link EI with value formation and ethical decision-making, citing conflict resolution and communication, but uses informal examples and lacks theoretical depth.",
