              "question_id": 2,
              "question": "Q2 How can Swami Vivekanandas\nidea of \"service to humanity is\nservice to God\" be linked to the\nsense of responsibility in public\nservants? Explain with examples\n(8 Marks)",
              "student_answer": "Ans: Swami Vivekanand believed\nthat \"service to humanity is\nservice to God\" which means as\na bureaucrat one should consider\ngiving service to people as\npure as giving service to God\nwe take this responsibility like\nwe serve our God.\n\nSense of responsibility in\npublic servants can be understood\nwith following points.\n\n1. Taking Duty as a sacred\nJob: Public servants don't see\ntheir duty like just a job",
              "student_answer_summary": "The student begins to explain Vivekananda's quote by equating public service to serving God and introduces the point of viewing duty as a sacred job, but leaves the answer incomplete without examples.",
